# Logger usage (frontend)

- Do not use `console.log`, `console.info`, `console.debug`, `console.warn`, or `console.error` in application code. The only place raw `console.*` is acceptable is inside `app/utils/logger.ts`.
- Import from `@/app/utils/logger`:
  - `log`, `logInfo`, `logDebug` ‚Äî verbose messages (development, or when `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_ENV` is `local` or `test`)
  - `logWarn` ‚Äî warnings (same gating as above)
  - `logError` ‚Äî always emitted (including production)
  - `logGroup` / `logGroupEnd` ‚Äî grouped logs (same gating as verbose)

## Examples

- Replace `console.log('payload', payload)` with `logInfo('payload', payload)`.
- Replace `console.warn('retrying', meta)` with `logWarn('retrying', meta)`.
- Replace `console.error('failed', err)` with `logError('failed', err)`.

## Rationale

Keeps production logs quiet while preserving errors and allowing structured local debugging.
